==English==

===Etymology===
From Turkish [[ibrik#Turkish|ibrik]] ‘ewer’ < Arabic {{ARchar|[[إبريق]]}} ''‘ibrīq'' < Persian {{FAchar|[[ابریز|آبریز]]}} ''ābrīz'' from {{FAchar|[[اب|آب]]}} ''āb'' ‘water’ + {{FAchar|[[ریز]]}} ''rīz'' ‘cup’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɪb'ri:k/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A long-spouted pitcher, typically made of brass. Occasionally confused with a Turkish coffee pot, which is properly called "[[jezve]]".

